    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">May</hi> 9, 1894.—Referred to the
                            Committee on Foreign Relations and ordered to be printed.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">To the Congress:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I transmit herewith a communication from the Secretary of State in regard
                            to recent dispatches from the U. S. minister at Honolulu, received since
                            my message of April 21, 1894, and also a dispatch from the minister
                            dated April 14, 1894.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grover Cleveland.</hi>
                    </signed>
                    <lb/>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Executive
                                        Mansion</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-09">
                                <hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                    1894</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft">The <hi rend="smallcaps">President</hi>:</p>
                    <p>The Secretary of State has the honor to lay before the President a
                                copy of a dispatch, with its accompaniment, from our minister at
                                Honolulu, No. 51, of April 14, 1894.</p>
                    <p>Mr. Willis’s dispatches, numbered 49 and 50, are dated April 13,
                                1894. The former acknowledges instructions numbered 17 to 21,
                                inclusive, and the latter transmits a receipt for the Department’s
                                cipher volume and holocryptic code.</p>
                    <p>Respectfully submitted.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q.
                                Gresham.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
